<div><h3>ENG 1570 - Literary Satire </h3>  <hr>This course will wxplore the literary genre known as satire. Questions we will discuss include: What is satire? Why do authors choose to use it? How does it differ from parody? Over the course of the semster we will read Johnathan Swift&#8217;s &#8220;A Modest Proposal,&#8221; George Orwell&#8217;s <em>Animal Farm</em>, Kurt Vonnegut&#8217;s <em>Cat&#8217;s Cradle,</em> and Aldous Huxley&#8217;s <em>Brave New World</em> to enhance our understanding of satire.<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Varies<br><br></div>		</td>
